        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 6:47PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 646 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Churubusco, or near Tri-lakes, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Churubusco, Lake Everett, and Collins.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
